rgy particle colliders [14]. For LWFAs operating in the quasilinear regime [2], the energy gain per stage varies as W ∝ E 0 L acc ∝ 1/n e , and the required length of the stage varies as L acc ∝ 1/n 3/2 e. Hence reaching higher energy gains requires the drive laser to propagate over longer lengths of lower density plasma. To date the highest reported electron energy generated in a LWFA is 4.2 GeV, which was achieved by guiding intense laser pulses through a 90 mm long plasma channel with an axial electron density of 7 × 10 17 cm −3 [15].},
